Google Student Ambassador Program – Game Night Edition 🎮
As part of the Google Student Ambassador Program, I participated in a Game Night session where we explored creative ways to build mini applications using Google tools.
During the first session, we used Google Canvas to design and develop a Snake and Ladder game. This was my first time working with Canvas, and it gave me a great introduction to its capabilities.
One of the most valuable takeaways from this experience was learning how to write clear and effective prompts. I discovered how better prompting can lead to more accurate results with fewer iterations, making the overall development process faster and more efficient.
I’m grateful for this opportunity to learn, experiment, and improve my practical skills through this program.
